definition: the outside and the inside/one's outward show and inner thoughts/exterior and interior
exterior surface/family relationship via females/to show (one's opinion)/a model/a table (listing information)/a form/a meter (measuring sth)

li, ancient measure of length, approx. 500 m/neighborhood/ancient administrative unit of 25 families/(Tw) borough, administrative unit between the township 鎮|镇[zhen4] and neighborhood 鄰|邻[lin2] levels
external appearance and inner thoughts coincide (idiom); to say what one means/to think and act as one
outside appearance and inner reality differ (idiom); not what it seems/saying one thing but meaning sth different

sentences.english: The worst personal development mistake didn't make the list.
sentences.chinese: 我没有把最糟糕的个人发展错误列进表里。

sentences.english: Am I consistent in my life?
sentences.chinese: 有没有过表里一致的信仰生活？

sentences.english: In the list the starred questions are the most difficult.
sentences.chinese: 在这张表里，加星号的问题是最难的。

sentences.english: It's not difficult for anyone to say "scorn", but almost impossible to behave the same as inner sense.
sentences.chinese: 不屑，说得容易，要做到表里一致并不容易。

sentences.english: But this double game is harder to maintain in the Internet era.
sentences.chinese: 但在互联网时代，这种表里不一的做法难以为继。

sentences.english: Triple energizer has no exterior-interior relationships with the zang-organs, it is therefore called "solitary fu-organ".
sentences.chinese: 三焦和脏之间没有表里关系，因此也称为“孤腑”。

sentences.english: We were married forty-nine years and I was always faithful.
sentences.chinese: 我们的婚姻维持了49年，我始终表里如一。

sentences.english: Kang Yuming, Kang Yuming, the original when your mind is hidden in this list.
sentences.chinese: 康雨明啊，康雨明，原来当年你的心思藏在这块表里。

sentences.english: The kidneys' meridians connect with the urinary bladder, with which they are internally-externally related.
sentences.chinese: 肾经与膀胱经相联系，构成表里关系。

sentences.english: It's all written on the brochure price list. I believe there will be one right for you.
sentences.chinese: 售价表里已经具体列明，我相信其中一定有适合你的。

sentences.english: Wasps in the third group suffered neither fate.
sentences.chinese: 第三组“表里如一”的胡蜂则没有受到任何攻击。

sentences.english: They're just going by hearsay and duplicating what they think the pro's are using.
sentences.chinese: 他们只是去的道听途说和重复表里如一亲的使用。

sentences.english: Madame Merle was not superficial-not she.
sentences.chinese: 梅尔夫人决不虚有其表，她是表里如一的。

sentences.english: Does your character have any sort of criminal record?
sentences.chinese: 你的角色是否表里不一？

sentences.english: Complementing each other, the two have much in common.
sentences.chinese: 二文互为表里，有不少一致之处。

sentences.english: For the soul is dead that slumbers, and things are not what they seem.
sentences.chinese: 因为沉睡的灵魂如死一般，事物的表里并不一样。

definition: half outside, half inside/half interior, half exterior
(TCM) the three truncal cavities (thoracic, abdominal and pelvic), known as the "triple heater" or "San Jiao"
"eight principles," a method of giving a general description and syndrome differentiation (TCM)
five viscera of TCM, namely: heart 心[xin1], liver 肝[gan1], spleen 脾[pi2], lungs 肺[fei4] and kidneys 腎|肾[shen4]
superficial syndrome/illness that has not attacked the vital organs of the human body

(TCM) six bowels (hollow organs), namely: gall bladder 膽|胆[dan3], stomach 胃[wei4], large intestine 大腸|大肠[da4 chang2], small intestine 小腸|小肠[xiao3 chang2], triple heater 三焦[san1 jiao1], bladder 膀胱[pang2 guang1]
one of the channels of TCM
